<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-29T17:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-29T17:49:00-05:00" n="489" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.38/54.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Blanchard</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-29T18:00:00-04:49">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1915—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Having received the invitation of the Haitian Government to enter into
                            modus vivendi, I accepted, stating my readiness to enter into modus
                            vivendi embodyng the same terms as the treaty. After numerous
                            conferences the following modus vivendi was agreed upon and in
                            accordance with your instructions was signed today at 6 p.m.</p>
                        <p>[Here follows the modus vivendi, identical with the inclosures with Mr.
                            Blanchard’s No. 51 of December 6; see post.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>